# Token Rules

## The Pipeline

```
tokens/tokens.json  →  npm run build:tokens  →  app/globals.css
```

- `tokens/tokens.json` is the **only** source of truth
- `tokens/build.mjs` runs Style Dictionary to generate CSS custom properties + Tailwind `@theme` block
- `app/globals.css` is **generated output — NEVER edit it directly**
- Run `npm run build:tokens` after any change to `tokens.json`

## W3C DTCG Format

Every token must have `$value`, `$type`, and `$description`:

```json
"cream": {
  "$value": "#f5e6d0",
  "$type": "color",
  "$description": "Warm background — primary surface colour"
}
```

## Token Groups

| Group | Purpose | Example variable |
|-------|---------|-----------------|
| `color` | Raw palette values | `--color-cream`, `--color-jade` |
| `semantic` | Role-based aliases | `--semantic-primary`, `--semantic-text` |
| `badUx` | Bad UX mode overrides | `--bad-ux-background` |
| `font` | Family, size, weight | `--font-size-base`, `--font-weight-bold` |
| `spacing` | Layout and padding | `--spacing-sm`, `--spacing-lg` |
| `radius` | Border radius | `--radius-sm`, `--radius-full` |
| `shadow` | Box shadows | `--shadow-card`, `--shadow-elevated` |

## The No-Naked-Values Rule

```tsx
// Correct
className="bg-[var(--color-cream)] p-[var(--spacing-md)] rounded-[var(--radius-sm)]"

// Wrong — naked values
className="bg-[#f5e6d0] p-4 rounded-lg"
```

If a value you need doesn't exist as a token, add it to `tokens.json` and rebuild — don't hardcode it.
